The esters were separated by a GC (Agilent 6890 N, USA) fitted with a capillary column (FFAP, 30 m, 0.25 mm i.d., 0.50-μm film thickness). Nitrogen was used as the carrier gas at an inlet pressure of 25 psi. The temperatures of the injection port and detector (FID) were maintained at 250 °C and 260 °C, respectively, and the temperature program for the column was as follows: 210 °C (1 min), increasing to 230 °C at 10 °C/min (22 min). The computer software used for statistical analysis was STATISTICA version 6.0 (Statsoft Inc., Oklahoma, USA). The peaks were identified based on their retention times using authentic standards of fatty acid methyl esters. The relative peak area was used for quantification of the contents of the fatty acids. The formula for calculating seed oil content was as follows:
